# Liquid Templating Guidelines

## Basic Syntax
- Use `{{ }}` for outputting variables
- Use `{% %}` for logic and control flow
- Use `{% comment %}` for comments

## Common Objects
- `{{ product.title }}`: Product title
- `{{ product.price | money }}`: Formatted price
- `{{ collection.products }}`: Collection products
- `{{ shop.name }}`: Store name
- `{{ customer.name }}`: Customer name

## Control Flow
```liquid
{% if product.available %}
  <button>Add to Cart</button>
{% else %}
  <p>Sold Out</p>
{% endif %}

{% for product in collection.products limit:10 %}
  <div>{{ product.title }}</div>
{% endfor %}
```

## Filters
- `| money`: Format as currency
- `| date`: Format dates
- `| truncate`: Truncate text
- `| split`: Split strings
- `| join`: Join arrays

## Snippets
Use `{% render 'snippet-name' %}` to include snippets
Pass variables: `{% render 'snippet-name', product: product %}`

## Best Practices
- Always check for object existence before accessing properties
- Use meaningful variable names
- Keep logic simple and readable
- Use comments to explain complex logic
- Avoid nested loops when possible
